ta bị dính liền ngay vào cây tre, không làm sao gỡ ra được. Ông thông gia thấy vậy chạy đến, định gỡ cho, nó lại đọc luôn: “Khắc nhập, khắc nhập”, thì cả ông cũng bị dính theo luôn, không lôi ra được nữa.\r\n\r\nHai họ thấy thế không còn ai dám lại gần nó nữa. Còn hai ông kia không còn biết làm thế nào đành van lạy xin nó thả ra cho. Ông chủ hứa gả con gái cho nó, ông thông gia xin về nhà ngay, nó để cho cả hai thề một hồi rồi nó mới đọc: “Khắc xuất, khắc xuất” thì hai ông rời ngay cây tre, và cây tre cũng rời ra trăm khúc.\r\n\r\nMọi người đều lấy làm khiếp phục đứa ở, ông chủ vội gả con gái cho nó, và từ đó không còn dám khinh thường nó nữa.', '', 'text evaluation', '<p>The text is a Vietnamese folk tale that tells the story of an elderly man who tricks his servant into performing tasks in exchange for marrying his daughter. The logical organization and flow of ideas in the text are clear and follow a coherent progression. The story begins by introducing the characters and their motivations. It then moves on to describe the servant\'s hard work and the subsequent betrayal by the wealthy man. The climax of the story occurs when the servant encounters an old man who helps him fulfill the impossible task given by the wealthy man. Finally, the resolution of the story is reached when the servant outsmarts both the wealthy man and the old man, leading to his marriage to the wealthy man\'s daughter.</p>\n<p>The transitions between sections are effective, as the narrative smoothly progresses from one event to another. The transitions help maintain the reader\'s understanding of the plot and keep them engaged in the story. The chronological order of events contributes to the overall coherence and readability of the text.</p>\n<p>To improve the structural flow, one recommendation would be to provide clearer differentiation between the dialogue and the overall narrative. Using quotation marks or indentations for dialogue would make it easier for the reader to distinguish between the characters\' speech and the narrator\'s description.</p>\n<p>In terms of clarity of language, word choice, and phrasing, the text is generally clear and concise. However, there are instances of vague or ambiguous terms that could affect the text\'s quality. For example, the phrase &quot;ông chủ&quot; is used multiple times throughout the text to refer to different characters, which could cause confusion for readers. Using more specific terms or providing additional context would enhance the clarity of the text.</p>\n<p>The use of precise language effectively communicates the intended message of the folk tale. The author uses descriptive language to paint a vivid picture of the characters and their actions. This helps immerse the reader in the story and enhances their understanding of the events.</p>\n<p>The text\'s tone is appropriate for its intended audience and purpose. The folk tale genre often incorporates a lighthearted and whimsical tone, which is evident in this text. The consistent use of colloquial language and informal expressions contributes to the tone and helps create an engaging reading experience. The tone aligns well with the topic of the story and enhances the reader\'s perception of the narrative.</p>\n<p>One alternative tone that could enhance impact or audience reception could be a more suspenseful or dramatic tone during critical moments of the story. By infusing moments of tension or surprise, the text could further captivate the reader and create a stronger emotional connection.</p>\n<p>The text successfully captures and maintains the reader\'s interest through its engaging storytelling style. The use of dialogue and descriptive language helps bring the characters and settings to life. The folk tale format itself is also inherently interesting, as it often presents unique scenarios and unexpected twists. However, there are areas that could benefit from additional engagement techniques, such as building suspense or creating more meaningful character development.</p>\n<p>In terms of originality and creativity, the text follows a conventional pattern of a folk tale. The story includes elements of trickery, hardship, and triumph, which are commonly found in folk tales across different cultures. While the overall structure and plot may not offer a fresh insight, the text showcases creativity in the specific details and interactions between characters. The use of imaginative imagery, such as the servant\'s ability to manipulate the tree, adds a unique perspective to the story.</p>\n<p>The text explores its main topic, the concept of trickery and its consequences, with a moderate level of depth. The content is relevant and specific to convey the various events that unfold. However, the text could benefit from providing more details and context around the motivations and emotions of the characters. Adding more depth to the characters\' thoughts and feelings would enrich the reader\'s understanding and connection to the story.</p>\n<p>The grammar, syntax, and vocabulary choices in the text are generally appropriate and contribute to readability. However, there are a few recurring errors and stylistic issues that could be addressed to enhance professionalism. For example, the inconsistent use of verb tenses and the lack of agreement between pronouns and antecedents undermine the text\'s professionalism. Proofreading for these errors would improve the overall quality of the text.</p>\n<p>The vocabulary choices in the text effectively convey the intended meanings. The author uses descriptive language to create imagery and evoke emotions. However, some phrases or expressions could be further clarified to ensure a better understanding for the reader. Additional explanations or synonyms could be provided for certain colloquial terms or expressions that may not be familiar to all readers.</p>\n<p>The text is tailored to its intended audience in terms of language and simplicity. The use of colloquial language and informal expressions aligns with the audience\'s familiarity and cultural context. However, adjustments could be made to improve the text\'s impact on its target audience. For example, providing more nuanced descriptions of the characters\' emotions and motivations would appeal to readers seeking deeper insights and character development.</p>\n<p>In conclusion, the text demonstrates a clear logical organization and flow of ideas. The language and phrasing are generally clear, but there are some areas that could benefit from greater clarity. The tone is appropriate for the intended audience and purpose, and it aligns well with the topic of the story. The text successfully captures and maintains the reader\'s interest, although additional engagement techniques could be incorporated. The originality and creativity of the text lie in the specific details and interactions between characters. The exploration of the main topic could be further deepened by providing more details and emotional depth. The text\'s grammar, syntax, and vocabulary choices are generally appropriate, but some recurring errors and stylistic issues could be addressed for improved readability and professionalism. Overall, the text is tailored to its intended audience, but adjustments could enhance its impact on the target audience.</p>', 'completed', 'wordifyai_6747e0cbea2239.03770743', '2024-11-27 20:17:31', '2024-11-27 20:17:31'),
(85, 9, 'Ngày xưa, có một ông già nhà quê có một cô gái đẹp. Trong nhà phải thuê một đầy tớ trai, ông ta muốn lợi dụng nó làm việc khỏi trả tiền, mới bảo nó rằng: “Mày chịu khó làm ăn với tao rồi tao gả con gái cho”. Người ở mừng lắm, ra sức làm lụng tới khuya không nề hà mệt nhọc. Nó giúp việc được ba năm, nhà ông ta mỗi ngày một giàu có.\r\n\r\nÔng nhà giàu không còn nghĩ đến lời hứa cũ nữa, đem con gái gả cho con một nhà phú hộ khác ở trong làng.\r\n\r\nSáng hôm sắp đưa dâu, ông chủ gọi đứa ở lên lừa nó một lần nữa, bảo rằng: “Bây giờ mày lên rừng tìm cho ra một cây tre có trăm đốt đem về đây làm đũa ăn cưới, thì tao cho mày lấy con gái tao ngay”.\r\n\r\nĐứa ở tưởng thật, vác dao đi rừng. Nó kiếm khắp nơi, hết rừng này qua rừng nọ, không tìm đâu thấy có cây tre đủ trăm đốt. Buồn khổ quá, nó ngồi một chỗ ôm mặt khóc. Bỗng thấy có một ông lão râu tóc bạc phơ, tay cầm gậy trúc hiện ra bảo nó: “Tại sao con khóc, hãy nói ta nghe, ta sẽ giúp cho”. Nó bèn đem đầu đuôi câu chuyện ông phú hộ hứa gả con gái cho mà kể lại. Ông lão nghe xong, mới bảo rằng: “Con đi chặt đếm đủ trăm cái đốt tre rồi đem lại đây ta bảo”.\r\n\r\nNó làm theo y lời dặn, ông dạy nó đọc: “Khắc nhập, khắc nhập” (vào ngay, vào ngay) đủ ba lần, thì một trăm khúc tre tự nhiên dính lại với nhau thành một cây trẻ đủ một trăm đốt. Nó mừng quá, định vác về, nhưng cây tre dài quá, vướng không đi được. Ông lão bảo nó đọc: “Khắc xuất, khắc xuất” (ra ngay, ra ngay) đúng ba lần thì cây tre trăm đốt lại rời ra ngay từng khúc.\r\n\r\nNó bèn bó cả lại mà gánh về nhà. Đến nơi thấy hai họ đang ăn uống vui vẻ, sắp đến lúc rước dâu, nó mới hay là ông chủ đã lừa nó đem gả con gái cho người ta rồi. Nó không nói gì, đợi lúc nhà trai đốt pháo cưới, bèn đem một trăm khúc tre xếp dài dưới đất, rồi lẩm bẩm đọc: “Khắc nhập, khắc nhập” cho liền lại thành một cây tre trăm đốt, đoạn gọi ông chủ đến bảo là đã tìm ra được, và đòi gả con gái cho nó. Ông chủ lấy làm lạ cầm cây tre lên xem, nó đọc luôn: “Khắc nhập, khắc nhập”, thì ông ta bị dính liền ngay vào cây tre, không làm sao gỡ ra được. Ông thông gia thấy vậy chạy đến, định gỡ cho, nó lại đọc luôn: “Khắc nhập, khắc nhập”, thì cả ông cũng bị dính theo luôn, không lôi ra được nữa.\r\n\r\nHai họ thấy thế không còn ai dám lại gần nó nữa. Còn hai ông kia không còn biết làm thế nào đành van lạy xin nó thả ra cho. Ông chủ hứa gả con gái cho nó, ông thông gia xin về nhà ngay, nó để cho cả hai thề một hồi rồi nó mới đọc: “Khắc xuất, khắc xuất” thì hai ông rời ngay cây tre, và cây tre cũng rời ra trăm khúc.', '<p>The text presented is a classic Vietnamese folktale that conveys moral lessons and cultural nuances through its narrative structure, character dynamics, and the use of magical realism. Below is an in-depth analysis that explores the text by addressing its main themes, structural flow, diction, and underlying messages.</p>\n<h3>Main Ideas and Underlying Meanings</h3>\n<p>The core themes revolve around exploitation, justice, and the balance of power. The story begins with an elderly farmer who seeks to benefit from the labor of a young servant. By promising marriage to his daughter, he manipulates the servant to work tirelessly without proper recompense. This initial unfairness sets the stage for the servant’s struggle.</p>\n<p>The climax reveals the elder\'s betrayal, as he fails to honor his promise and instead gives his daughter to another man. This act of treachery instills a sense of injustice that resonates with the reader, reflecting common societal issues of exploitation and broken promises. The servant’s subsequent quest for a hundred-segment bamboo stick symbolizes resilience, as he does not succumb to despair; rather, he seeks help, representing human agency and resourcefulness when faced with oppression.</p>\n<p>The introduction of the wise old man aligns with common folkloric motifs, where magical assistance is bestowed upon the worthy, emphasizing community, wisdom, and tradition. This moment illuminates the theme of seeking help from others, grounding the notion that individuals are not alone in their struggles.</p>\n<h3>Organization and Flow</h3>\n<p>The text flows in a coherent manner that mirrors traditional storytelling. It begins with the setup of the initial situation—the elder’s manipulative tactics and the relationship dynamics between him and the servant. The subsequent development recounts the servant\'s search for the bamboo, highlighting his dedication to his goal and culminating in his encounter with the magical old man. </p>\n<p>The climax unfolds with the servant’s clever use of magic to trap the elder and his accomplice, a form of poetic justice. Finally, the resolution arrives when the two men are forced to promise the servant his rightful claim to the farmer\'s daughter, emphasizing the return to the rightful order.</p>\n<p>By maintaining a linear progression, the narrative allows the reader to invest emotionally in the servant’s plight while also drawing a clear parallel to his reward and the consequences faced by the elder.</p>\n<h3>Diction and Language Usage</h3>\n<p>The language utilized in the tale is straightforward and accessible, consistent with oral storytelling traditions. The repeated phrases “Khắc nhập, khắc nhập” and “Khắc xuất, khắc xuất” are pivotal and striking in their simplicity. These phrases not only serve a functional role within the plot but also add a rhythmic quality that enhances memorability.</p>\n<p>The choice of words also reflects cultural elements, grounding the story in its Vietnamese context while engaging universal themes of greed, justice, and resolution. The depiction of the characters through descriptive terms such as “ông già nhà quê” (old farmer) evokes imagery of rural life and traditional values, creating a tangible setting.</p>\n<h3>Sentence Patterns and Grammatical Techniques</h3>\n<p>Sentence structure within the folktale varies between simple declarative sentences that convey the narrative and more elaborate constructions during moments of tension or emotional resonance. The effective use of dialogue adds a dynamic element that advances the plot and enhances character interactions.</p>\n<p>Grammatically, the text mirrors colloquial speech patterns, suggesting authenticity and relatability. The playful manipulation of language, particularly in the incantations, emphasizes the narrative\'s magical realism while mirroring the character\'s trials and triumphs. This alignment of grammar with content underscores the story\'s moral underpinning—the assertion of individual rights against unethical power dynamics.</p>\n<h3>Themes and Nuances</h3>\n<p>Delving deeper, the story examines the notion of power and its cyclical nature. The farmer initially holds power over the servant due to his wealth and social status, but this dynamic shifts as the servant gains magical assistance. The tale implicitly suggests that true power lies in honor, justice, and respect for promises. The elder’s ultimate entrapment symbolizes the inevitable consequences of his deceptive practices.</p>\n<p>Additionally, the resolution reinforces the concept of social contracts. The entrapment of both the elder and his son-in-law highlights the importance of integrity in relationships—once broken, the repercussions can be severe. The servant\'s eventual success represents a restoration of balance, signaling that good fortune and justice can prevail against deceit.</p>\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>This Vietnamese folktale encapsulates complex themes of exploitation, justice, and redemption through its rich narrative structure, relatable diction, and character portrayals. The integration of magical realism serves not only as an entertaining element but as a profound reminder of cultural ideals regarding honor and justice. The servant\'s journey reflects resilience and cleverness, celebrating the universal struggle against oppression and the pursuit of fairness, ultimately resonating with audiences across generations.</p>\n<p>In conclusion, the tale’s depth is revealed through a multilayered exploration of character dynamics, societal structures, and the impacts of choices, making it a timeless piece reflective of collective human experiences.</p>', 'text analysis', '', 'completed', 'wordifyai_6750f5b2e1fa05.34932233', '2024-12-04 17:37:06', '2024-12-04 17:37:06');
INSERT INTO `text_analysis` (`id`, `user_id`, `text_content`, `analysis_result`, `type_of_analysis`, `evaluation`, `status`, `analysis_evaluation_code`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
